<subSubSection pageId="79" pageNumber="80" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="79.[151,1437,151,1315]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1182,1207]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Comments.</emphasis>
The only other species in 
<taxonomicName box="[631,810,1182,1207]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pelecinobaccha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Diptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[631,810,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Pelecinobaccha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with dense black pile on the thorax are 
<taxonomicName box="[1258,1361,1182,1207]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Baccha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilipes">
<emphasis box="[1258,1272,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1286,1361,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">pilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pelecinobaccha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Diptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilinigridensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P. pilinigridensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Neither of these species has the frontal triangle pollinosity or the confluent antennal insertions of the 
<typeStatus box="[194,292,1254,1279]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[332,429,1255,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Baccha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[332,349,1255,1278]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[365,429,1255,1278]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[497,595,1254,1279]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">holotype</typeStatus>
has its head glued to the thorax raising the possibility that it is actually a composite.
</paragraph>
